locality: Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Northern Fartak Mts, dissected table-land near the track W below J. Karmoum (with the disused radio tower). Relevé A27: Rocky slope (incl. 25°) with small rock ledges, dwarf shrub vegetation dominating. Alt.: 600-650 m. 8.10.2001, Leg.: P. Hein, H. Kürschner & M. Reisch YP 1090.

Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. upper Wadi Hajar, 2 km S of the village Mintaq, broad wadi with brackish soil. Dense cushion, 50 cm diameter. Alt.: 450-480 m. 15.11.1999, Leg.: P. Hein, M. Al-Mashjary & N. Kilian PH 6363.
Prov. Kerman: Khabr va Rouchun protected region, 50km SSW of Baft.
Iraq: Distr. Diyala: Ad confines Persiae. In collibus conglomeraticis ab oppido Mandali, ca. 10km orientem versus.
Oman: Northern Oman, Jabal Akhdar range, track from Al Hamra via Ghul and Al Khateem up to Jabal Shams, 23°13'N, 57°07'E, 750-1400 m. Alt.: 750-1400 m. 13.10.1998, Leg.: N. Kilian & P. Hein NK 5627.
Yemen: Socotra. near the Hawlaf port, 8 km E of Hadibu. Alt.: 10 m. 27.3.1996, Leg.: P. Hein & E. von Raab-Straube PH 401.
Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. Jol plateau, some km W of Ghail-bin-Yemen. On clay. Alt.: 870 m. 18.9.2001, Leg.: N. Kilian, P. Hein & M. A. Hubaishan YP 172.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Jabal Sharwayn 10 km W of Qeshn, rocky slopes and plateau looking on the Qeshn plain. Rocky slopes, strongly affected by the monsoonal mist: succulent rich Euphorbia balsamifera zone. Alt.: 180 m. 24.9.1998, Leg.: P. Hein, S. A. Ghazanfar & N. Kilian PH 4889.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. NE flank of Jabal Fartak, lower part of the Wadi Nishtun 2 km S of the town Nishtun. Wadi vegetation with Acacia trees, shrubs and climbers, on gravelly sandy substrate. Alt.: 70-100 m. 16.11.2000, Leg.: P. Hein, N. Kilian & C. Naumann PH 8237.
